The paper discusses the use of Intel SGX enclaves for secure deep learning inference-as-a-service, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on deep learning models and their performance, which suggests a possible fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of a system, which could potentially fit under software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories.
